      "acceptanceCriteria": "The hemolysis damage model (power-law or mechanistic) must be justified against literature and sensitivity of predicted hemolysis index to model-form choice must be quantified.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model was adopted without comparison to alternative hemolysis models (e.g., Faghih-Sharp). Model-form uncertainty was not quantified. Factor not assessed; critical epistemic gap. Achieved level 1."
